'''Kitaya Inari Shrine''' (北谷稲荷神社) is a {{ill|Shinto shrine|ja|神社|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shinto shrine|qq=}} located in Jinnan, Shibuya, Tokyo.

== History ==

The exact year of establishment is unknown. However, records such as the {{ill|Munafuda|ja|棟札|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Munafuda|qq=}} from the reconstruction after significant damage in {{ill|1660|ja|万治3年|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1660|qq=}} and descriptions in the {{ill|Newly Edited Musashi Fudoki Manuscript|ja|新編武蔵風土記稿|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Newly Edited Musashi Fudoki Manuscript|qq=}} (compiled between {{ill|1810|ja|1810年|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1810|qq=}} and {{ill|1830|ja|1830年|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1830|qq=}})<ref>{{cite book|ja|title=新編武蔵風土記稿|volume=Volume 10, Toshima District, Upper Shibuya Village|publisher=Geographical Bureau, Ministry of Interior|date=1884-06|id={{NDLJP|763976/81}}}}</ref> indicate that the shrine may have been established as early as the {{ill|Bunmei era (1469–1486)|ja|文明|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Bunmei era (1469–1486)|qq=}}. The shrine was possibly moved from Suruga Province and enshrined in the northeastern corner of the premises at that time.<ref name="A">[http://www.tokyo-jinjacho.or.jp/syoukai/06_shibuya/list.html Tokyo Shrine Association: Shibuya Ward Shrines]</ref>

The shrine was rebuilt in {{ill|1997|ja|1997年|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1997|qq=}} with a modern design by the architectural firm led by {{ill|Kikutake Kiyonori|ja|菊竹清訓|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kikutake Kiyonori|qq=}}.

== Enshrined Deities ==

The shrine honors the following main deities:<ref name="A"></ref>
* {{ill|Ukanomitama|lt=Uka-no-Mitama-no-Ōkami|ja|宇迦之霊大神|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ukanomitama|qq=}} (associated with {{ill|Inari Ōkami|ja|稲荷神|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Inari Ōkami|qq=}})
* {{ill|Ōkuninushi|lt=Ōnamuchi-no-Mikoto|ja|大己貴大神|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōkuninushi|qq=}} (another name for {{ill|Ōkuninushi|ja|大国主|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōkuninushi|qq=}})
* {{ill|Ōmiya-no-Me|lt=Ōmiya-no-Me|lt=Omiyanome|lt=Ōmiya-no-Me|lt=Ōmiyahime-no-Mikoto|ja|大宮比賣大神|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Omiyanome|qq=}}
* {{ill|Empress Jingū|ja|神功皇后|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Empress Jingū|qq=}} (consort of {{ill|Emperor Chūai|ja|仲哀天皇|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Emperor Chūai|qq=}})
* {{ill|Otanomikoto|Ōta-no-Mikoto|ja|大田命|1=Ōta-no-Mikoto|2=ja|3=太田命|4=fr|5=大田命|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Otanomikoto|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōta-no-Mikoto|qq=}} (a deity of {{ill|longevity|ja|長寿|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/longevity|qq=}} and {{ill|arts|ja|芸能|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/arts|qq=}})

== Features ==

* The shrine is located between {{ill|Shibuya Koen-dori Avenue|ja|渋谷公園通り|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shibuya Koen-dori Avenue|qq=}} to the west and {{ill|Fire-dori Avenue|ja|ファイヤー通り|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Fire-dori Avenue|qq=}} to the east. The surrounding area is a bustling {{ill|commercial district|ja|繁華街|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/commercial district|qq=}} with nearby landmarks such as the {{ill|NHK Broadcasting Center|ja|NHK放送センター|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/NHK Broadcasting Center|qq=}} and Shibuya Ward Office.<ref>[http://www.koen-dori.com/townmap/a3.html 渋谷公園通り Town Map]</ref>
* Notable monuments in the precinct include a stone erected by farmers in {{ill|1909|ja|明治42nd year|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1909|qq=}} during the establishment of a training ground and a flood control monument commemorating the {{ill|1920|ja|1920年|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1920|qq=}} flood of the {{ill|Udagawa River|ja|宇田川|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Udagawa River|qq=}}.<ref group="note">During the Meiji period, the surrounding area was under the management of the Ministry of War and used for training grounds.</ref>

== Parish District ==

The shrine serves the following areas in Shibuya:
* {{ill|Jinnan|ja|神南|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Jinnan|qq=}}
* {{ill|Udagawachō|ja|宇田川町|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Udagawachō|qq=}} (Blocks 1–13, parts of 14 and 15)
* {{ill|Shibuya 1-chome|ja|渋谷一丁目|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shibuya 1-chome|qq=}} (Blocks 21–23)
* {{ill|Jingūmae 6-chome|ja|神宮前六丁目|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Jingūmae 6-chome|qq=}} (Blocks 12, 14, parts of 5–19, 21–26, and parts of 27)
* {{ill|Jingūmae 1-chome|ja|神宮前一丁目|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Jingūmae 1-chome|qq=}} (Blocks 7–9, parts of 14, and 16–20, including {{ill|Takeshita Street|ja|竹下通り|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Takeshita Street|qq=}} in Harajuku)

== Nearest Stations ==

; {{ill|Shibuya Station|ja|渋谷駅|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shibuya Station|qq=}} (major terminal station)
: Served by:
* {{ill|JR East|ja|東日本旅客鉄道|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/JR East|qq=}}: {{ill|Yamanote Line|ja|山手線|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yamanote Line|qq=}}, {{ill|Saikyō Line|ja|埼京線|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Saikyō Line|qq=}}, {{ill|Shōnan-Shinjuku Line|ja|湘南新宿ライン|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shōnan-Shinjuku Line|qq=}}, {{ill|Narita Express|ja|成田エクスプレス|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Narita Express|qq=}}
* {{ill|Tōkyū Corporation|ja|東急電鉄|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tōkyū Corporation|qq=}}: {{ill|Tōkyū Tōyoko Line|ja|東急東横線|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tōkyū Tōyoko Line|qq=}}, {{ill|Tōkyū Den-en-toshi Line|ja|東急田園都市線|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tōkyū Den-en-toshi Line|qq=}}
* {{ill|Keiō Corporation|ja|京王電鉄|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Keiō Corporation|qq=}}: {{ill|Keiō Inokashira Line|ja|井の頭線|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Keiō Inokashira Line|qq=}}
* {{ill|Tokyo Metro|ja|東京メトロ|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tokyo Metro|qq=}}: {{ill|Ginza Line|ja|東京メトロ銀座線|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ginza Line|qq=}}, {{ill|Hanzōmon Line|ja|東京メトロ半蔵門線|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hanzōmon Line|qq=}}, {{ill|Fukutoshin Line|ja|東京メトロ副都心線|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Fukutoshin Line|qq=}}

